{[%evp 0,40,28,28,48,48,79,46,64,36,41,42,29,32,27,27,22,31,40,31,8,8,13,22,17, 29,21,18,15,5,9,1,0,-30,-4,-20,0,-3,22,-7,13,23,23]} 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. Nc3 d5 4. Bb5+ {This check is less dangerous than after the intermediate exchange on d5, examined later.} Bd7 5. Bxd7+ (5. e5 {is examined in Line 4.}) 5... Qxd7 6. exd5 {This attempt at gaining an advance in development is ineffective.} (6. e5 {is examined in Line 3.}) (6. d3 {is solid, but does not promise much.} Nc6 7. Bg5 (7. O-O e6 8. Bf4 Bd6 $5 $146 9. e5 Bc7 $1 $11) 7... d4 {After White has made an important commitment on the previous move, this makes sense.} 8. Ne2 (8. Bxf6 gxf6 9. Nb1 h5 10. g3 e6 11. Nbd2 O-O-O 12. Nc4 f5 $5 13. exf5 exf5 14. O-O h4 $5 15. Nxh4 f4 $44) 8... Ng8 $1 9. c3 f6 10. Bc1 {Fatkhutdinov, G (2349) -Kazakov,K (2293) Pavlodar Gold Product 2014 (8) 1/2-1/2} e5 11. O-O O-O-O 12. cxd4 cxd4 13. Ng3 Kb8 14. a3 Rc8 15. b4 Nd8 16. Nd2 Ne6 $11) 6... Nxd5 7. Nxd5 Qxd5 8. d4 (8. O-O Nc6 {allows Black to stabilise the position and retain a space advantage.} 9. d3 g6 10. Qe2 Bg7 11. c3 O-O 12. Be3 e5 $15 { Ladron de Guevara Pinto,P (2424) -Rakhmanov,A (2627) Titled Tuesday intern op 5th June blitz 2018 (1) 0-1}) 8... e6 9. Be3 {Trying to force Black's hand.} ( 9. O-O {offers Black a tempo for increasing his pressure in the centre.} Nc6 ( 9... c4 10. Bf4 $5 $14) 10. dxc5 (10. Be3 cxd4 11. Nxd4 Be7 $11) 10... Qxd1 11. Rxd1 Bxc5 12. Bf4 Ke7 {Black does not have any problems at all.} 13. c3 Rhd8 14. b4 Bd6 15. Bxd6+ Rxd6 16. Rxd6 Kxd6 17. Rd1+ Ke7 18. Kf1 Rc8 19. Ke2 f6 $11 {Turgut,A (2156) -Dardha,D (2316) Wch U14 Porto Carras 2018 (8) 0-1}) 9... c4 { This ambitious move, aiming to reach a blockade on the light squares, is possible after White's commitment on the previous move.} (9... cxd4 {is entirely playable, though.} 10. Qxd4 Qxd4 11. Nxd4 a6 $11) 10. O-O ({With the king in the centre,} 10. Bf4 {is ineffective due to} Qe4+ $1 11. Be3 Bd6) 10... Bd6 11. b3 (11. Qe2 Nd7 12. a4 O-O 13. Nd2 Rac8 14. b3 c3 15. Nf3 Nf6 16. h3 Qe4 17. Ne1 Nd5 $15 {Marholev,D (2423) -Okhotnik,V (2404) Le Touquet op 20th 2005 (5) 0-1}) 11... Nd7 (11... O-O 12. bxc4 Qxc4 13. Nd2 Qc7 14. h3 Nc6 15. c4 Rfd8 16. Qb3 Be7 17. Nf3 Bf6 $11) ({The most ambitious continuation is} 11... b5 $5 {not fearing} 12. a4 O-O 13. axb5 cxb3 $11) 12. bxc4 Qxc4 13. Nd2 Qc7 14. h3 (14. Qg4 {is more critical.} f5 $1 15. Qxg7 (15. Qh5+ g6 16. Qh3 O-O-O $13) 15... O-O-O 16. Nf3 Rhg8 17. Qf7 f4 18. Bd2 Qc6 19. Kh1 e5 $44) 14... O-O 15. c4 Rac8 16. Qf3 Bb4 (16... f5 $5) 17. Rac1 Qc6 18. Ne4 Be7 19. Rfd1 f5 20. d5 ( 20. Nd2 Qxf3 21. Nxf3 Nb6 $11) 20... Qa6 $13 {Maksimovic,B (2445) -Le,T (2514) Titled Tuesday intern op 10th May Early blitz 2022 (6) 0-1} * 

