1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. Nc3 d5 4. Bb5+ Bd7 5. Bxd7+ Qxd7 6. e5 {This is a completely different approach than in the previous line. White forces his opponent to waste time with his knight, since the d7-square is unavailable. However, the previous exchange of the light-squared bishops favours Black from a strategic point of view.} Ng8 {After...e7-e6 and ...Nge7, the knight will find itself on a good path.} 7. d4 {It does not make sense to refrain from this move.} (7. O-O Nc6 8. Re1 e6 9. Ne2 Nge7 10. d3 Ng6 11. Nf4 Be7 12. Nh5 O-O 13. c3 {Romanov,E (2599) -Le,T (2501) Titled Tuesday intern op 7th July blitz 2020 (8) 0-1} b5 $15) 7... e6 8. O-O Nc6 9. Ne2 {White needs to consolidate the central squares. The queen's knight prepares for a re-capture on d4, in order to keep the pawn on e5 defended by the king's knight.} (9. Bf4 {exposes the bishop and indirectly, the pawn on e5.} cxd4 10. Nxd4 Nge7 11. Ncb5 Ng6 12. Bg3 h5 $1 {Before taking on e5, Black does best to deprive the queen of the square on h5.} (12... Bc5 13. Nb3 Be7 14. Nd6+ Bxd6 15. exd6 $13 { Bethke,R (2366) -Le,T (2514) Titled Tuesday intern op 14th Jun Early blitz 2022 (5) 0-1}) (12... Ngxe5 13. Nxc6 bxc6 14. Bxe5 cxb5 15. Qh5 $44) 13. h3 h4 14. Bh2 Ngxe5 15. Nxc6 bxc6 16. Bxe5 cxb5 17. Qg4 f6 $17) 9... cxd4 10. Nexd4 Bc5 {Abstractly, maintaining the tension is the best idea.} (10... Nxd4 { is entirely playable, though.} 11. Nxd4 Ne7 12. Be3 (12. Qg4 Rc8 13. c3 { Movsesian,S (2647) -Rakhmanov,A (2653) Wch Rapid Riadh 2017 (8) 0-1} Ng6 14. f4 Bc5 15. Be3 O-O 16. Rae1 Bxd4 17. Bxd4 Ne7 18. Qe2 Rc4 19. g4 Nc6 20. Rd1 Nxd4 21. cxd4 Qe7 $132 {[%cal Gf8c8]}) 12... Nc6 13. Nxc6 Qxc6 14. Qg4 a6 15. Rac1 Rc8 16. c3 Qc4 17. Qxc4 Rxc4 18. b3 Rc6 $11 {Anand,V (2759) -Mamedyarov,S  (2808) Leuven GCT blitz 2018 (2) 1/2-1/2}) 11. Nb3 (11. c3 Nge7 12. Bg5 (12. Re1 Bb6 $5 13. Bf4 Nxd4 14. cxd4 Nc6 15. Be3 Rc8 16. Rc1 O-O $11 {Boudreau,D  (1962) -Caire,F (2186) Quebec Carnaval op 2006 (2) 0-1}) 12... O-O 13. Re1 Nxd4 14. cxd4 Bb6 15. Bxe7 Qxe7 16. Re3 Rfc8 17. Rc1 Qd7 18. Rec3 Rxc3 19. Rxc3 Rc8 20. Qc2 Rxc3 21. Qxc3 Qc7 22. Qxc7 Bxc7 23. Kf1 f6 24. exf6 gxf6 25. Ke2 Kf7 $11 {Kubicka,A (2256) -Hansen,M (2058) Titled Tuesday intern op 28th Apr blitz 2020 (8) 1-0}) 11... Bb6 12. a4 a6 13. a5 Ba7 14. c3 Nge7 15. h4 $6 {Just wasting time.} (15. Re1 $11) 15... O-O 16. h5 $6 f6 $1 17. exf6 Rxf6 $15 { Vachier Lagrave,M (2736) -Le,T (2542) Titled Tuesday intern op 28th Mar Early blitz 2023 (8) 1-0} * 

