{[%evp 0,40,21,14,63,56,59,55,55,63,73,81,51,46,60,63,69,72,77,57,52,62,77,78, 76,60,52,44,67,36,56,46,40,48,38,62,46,52,70,24,27,27,32]} 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. Nc3 e6 4. d4 d5 5. exd5 {The most direct attempt at reaching an advance in development.} Nxd5 6. Bd3 (6. Bc4 Nxc3 7. bxc3 {transposes to Line 6.}) (6. Bb5+ {may be answered with} Bd7 (6... Nc6 {transposes to Line 11.}) 7. Bxd7+ Qxd7 $11) 6... Nc6 {One of the good moves.} (6... cxd4 7. Nxd4 (7. Nb5 Bb4+ 8. Bd2 Nc6 9. Nbxd4 Nxd4 10. Nxd4 O-O 11. O-O Bxd2 12. Qxd2 e5 13. Nf3 Nf4 14. Rfe1 Nxd3 15. Qxd3 Qxd3 16. cxd3 f6 17. d4 {Nagy,G (2411) -Fang,Y (2365) Kecskemet Caissa IM 01 2015 (7) 1/2-1/2}) 7... Nxc3 8. bxc3 Nd7 9. O-O Nc5 $1 $146 (9... Be7 $2 10. Qg4 Bf6 11. Ba3 $16 {Darias Darias,L (1816) -Ruiz Yanes, J (1494) Santa Cruz Promocion CajaCanarias 8th 2015 (6.2) 1-0}) 10. Qg4 (10. Ba3 Nxd3 $5 11. Bxf8 Kxf8 12. cxd3 g6 $11) 10... h5 11. Qg3 h4 12. Qg4 h3 $11 13. g3 $2 Qd5 $17) (6... Nxc3 $6 7. bxc3 {leads to a position we avoid in Line 5.}) 7. Nxd5 exd5 {A comfortable version of the Isolani. There is no knight to pin on f6 and Black controls d4 quite well.} 8. O-O (8. dxc5 Bxc5 9. O-O O-O 10. h3 Qf6 11. c3 Bf5 $11) (8. Qe2+ Qe7 9. dxc5 Qxe2+ 10. Kxe2 Bxc5 11. Be3 Bxe3 12. Kxe3 {Salinas Herrera,P (2532) -Altman,J (2095) Philadelphia int op 15th 2022 (8) 1-0} Bg4 13. Nd4 Kd7 (13... O-O-O $11) 14. c3 (14. Bb5 Rhe8+ 15. Kd2 Kd6 $11) 14... Rhe8+ $11) 8... c4 (8... cxd4 $5 $146 {is also playable.} 9. Bb5 (9. Bg5 f6 10. Re1+ Be7 11. Bf4 O-O $11) 9... Be7 10. Nxd4 Bd7 11. c3 O-O 12. Be3 Re8 13. Qh5 Bf6 14. Bd3 (14. Qxd5 Re5 15. Qc4 Nxd4 16. Bxd7 Rxe3 17. fxe3 Nc2 $11) 14... h6 15. Qxd5 Bxd4 16. Bxd4 Be6 17. Qe4 (17. Qxd8 Raxd8 18. Rfd1 Nxd4 19. cxd4 Re7 20. Rd2 Red7 21. Rad1 Bxa2 $11) 17... g6 {Threatening .. .Bxa2.} 18. Rfe1 Nxd4 19. cxd4 Qb6 20. b3 Rad8 $11) 9. Re1+ Be7 10. Bf1 O-O 11. c3 (11. b3 Be6 $1 12. bxc4 $5 (12. h3 b5 $11) 12... dxc4 13. Rxe6 $5 {This and the previous move are White's only possibility of fighting for an advantage.} fxe6 14. Bxc4 Kh8 15. Bxe6 Rxf3 16. gxf3 Qxd4 17. Qxd4 Nxd4 18. Bd5 Ne2+ 19. Kg2 Bf6 20. Rb1 Rd8 21. c4 Nxc1 22. Rxc1 b5 $11) 11... Bg4 12. g3 Qd7 13. Bg2 { Rabiega, R (2527) -Huebner,R (2604) GER-ch Internet g/5' blitz 2004 (2) 0-1} b5 14. Bf4 a5 $11 * 

