{[%evp 0,40,31,31,50,62,68,69,85,42,68,62,69,48,56,51,73,56,56,50,47,55,96,71, 74,70,72,51,66,37,42,47,54,64,53,45,77,59,71,27,27,18,36]} 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. Nc3 e6 4. d4 d5 5. exd5 Nxd5 6. Nxd5 {A consequent continuation.} Qxd5 7. Be3 {Continuing the developing policy.} (7. Bb5+ Bd7 8. Bxd7+ Nxd7 $11) (7. c4 Qd8 $1 {takes the steam out of White's initiativee, leaving him with certain weaknesses on dark squares.} 8. Bg5 (8. d5 Bd6 $5 $146) (8. Be3 cxd4 9. Qxd4 Bb4+) 8... f6 9. Be3 cxd4 10. Qxd4 Bb4+ 11. Bd2 Nc6 (11... Qxd4 12. Nxd4 Bxd2+ 13. Kxd2 {Iob,A (1161) -Angus,G (1935) IECG CP.2000.P.00028 0-1} Bd7 14. f4 Nc6 15. Nxc6 Bxc6 $11) 12. Qxd8+ Kxd8 13. O-O-O Ke7 $11) 7... cxd4 8. Qxd4 (8. Nxd4 a6 9. Be2 e5 10. Bf3 (10. Nb3 Qxg2 11. Bf3 Qg6 $13) 10... Qa5+ 11. Bd2 Qc7 $146 12. Qe2 Bd6 $11) 8... Qxd4 9. Nxd4 a6 10. O-O-O (10. Be2 {, preventing Black's plan in the main line, also dserves mentioning.} e5 11. Nb3 (11. Nf3 Nc6 12. Bc4 Bf5 13. O-O-O f6 14. Rhe1 Rc8 15. c3 b5 $132) 11... Nc6 12. O-O-O Bf5 13. c3 (13. Nc5 Nb4 14. Nxb7 Rb8 15. Nd6+ Bxd6 16. Rxd6 Nxa2+ $11 17. Kb1 Nc3+ 18. Ka1 Nxe2 19. Re1 Bxc2 20. Rxe2 Bb3 21. Bb6 f6 22. Re3 Bf7 23. f4 O-O $11) 13... Rc8 14. Bf3 (14. Nc5 Nd4 15. Bxd4 exd4 16. Nxb7 dxc3 17. Bxa6 cxb2+ 18. Kxb2 Rc2+ 19. Kb3 Rxf2 20. Rhe1+ Be6+ 21. Bc4 Be7 $11) (14. Rhe1 Nb4 $132) 14... f6 (14... Nb4 15. Bxb7 $16) 15. Nc5 (15. Rhe1 Be7 16. Nc5 h5 17. Nxb7 Nb4 $11) 15... Bxc5 16. Bxc5 h5 (16... e4 17. Bh5+ $14 Bg6 $6 18. Bg4 $16) 17. Rd6 (17. h3 e4 18. Bxe4 Bxe4 19. Rhe1 Ne5 20. Rxe4 Rxc5 21. f4 O-O $11) 17... Kf7 18. Re1 g5 19. a4 Kg6 20. Bb6 Rh7 $5 (20... Rhe8 21. Bd5 Nb4 22. Bxb7 Nd3+ 23. Rxd3 Bxd3 24. Bxc8 Rxc8 25. Kd2 Bc4 26. Kc2 Bd5 27. g3 Kf5 $44) 21. b3 g4 22. Be2 Rd7 $11) 10... b6 $5 $146 {The safest. Black prepares ...Bb7, without exposing his queenside too much.} (10... Be7 $6 11. Be2 O-O $6 (11... e5 12. Nb3 Nc6 13. Nc5 $14) 12. Rhe1 Nd7 13. f4 $16 {Rapport,R (2735) -Shankland,S (2731) Saint Louis Champions Showdown blitz 2019 (21.5) 1-0}) (10... Bd7 $6 {I will give Nimzowitsch's game in full since it contains many interesting moments in the endgame. It is just for fun and not for theory's sake.} 11. Be2 Nc6 12. Bf3 ( 12. Nb3 $1) 12... Bc5 (12... O-O-O 13. Nxc6 Bxc6 14. Rxd8+ Kxd8 15. Bxc6 bxc6 16. Rd1+ Kc8 17. Rd3 Be7 18. Rb3 Bd8 $11 {Fogarasi,T (2360) -Dory,J (2320) Budapest Utasellato IM 1988 (8) 1/2-1/2}) 13. Nxc6 Bxe3+ 14. fxe3 Bxc6 15. Bxc6+ bxc6 16. Rd6 Rc8 17. Rhd1 h5 $1 18. R1d4 (18. Rd7 Rh6 19. Ra7 Rf6 20. b3 Rf2 21. Rd2 Rf1+ 22. Kb2 $18) 18... Rh6 19. Rc4 Rf6 20. Rcxc6 Rxc6 21. Rxc6 Rf1+ 22. Kd2 Rf2+ 23. Kd3 (23. Kc3 Rxg2 24. Rxa6 Rxh2 25. a4 h4 26. a5 Rh1 27. Ra8+ Ke7 28. b4 $18) 23... Rxg2 24. Rxa6 Rxh2 25. a4 h4 26. a5 Rh1 27. Ra8+ Ke7 28. Rh8 (28. b4 Rd1+ $1 {[%cal Gd1d8]} 29. Ke2 Rd8) 28... g5 29. b4 Ra1 (29... Rd1+ 30. Kc4 Rd8 31. Rh6 Ra8 $5 $13) (29... Kd6 $11) 30. Ke4 (30. c4 $18) 30... Kd6 31. c4 $2 (31. Rd8+ Kc7 32. Rh8 $11) 31... f5+ $1 32. Kd3 g4 $1 33. c5+ ( 33. Rxh4 g3) 33... Kc6 (33... Ke7 34. Rxh4 g3 35. Rh7+ Kf6 36. Rh6+ Kf7 37. Rh7+ Kg6 38. Rh8 Kg7 $2 39. Rh3 f4 40. Rh4 $1 f3 41. Rg4+ Kh7 42. Rxg3 f2 43. Rf3 f1=Q+ 44. Rxf1 Rxf1 45. a6) 34. Rc8+ Kd7 35. Rh8 g3 36. b5 g2 37. c6+ Kd6 38. Rd8+ Ke7 39. Rg8 g1=Q 40. Rxg1 Rxg1 41. a6 Kd6 {Perlis,J-Nimzowitsch,A Karlsbad-02 International Masters 1911 (22) 0-1}) (10... b5 {exposes Black to} 11. c4 {, even though it is unclear whether that is bad.} bxc4 12. Bxc4 Nd7 13. Kb1 Bb7 14. f3 Be7) (10... e5 {does not work with the white bishop on f1 still. } 11. Nf3 Nc6 12. Bc4 $1 {Without a previous loss of time.} Be7 13. Rhe1 $14 { With perfect centralisation.}) 11. Be2 Bb7 12. Rhe1 Nd7 (12... Bxg2 $6 13. f3 $1) 13. g3 (13. g4 Nf6 $11) (13. Bh5 g6 14. Bf3 Bxf3 15. Nxf3 b5 16. Bd4 Rg8 17. h4 h6 18. c3 Rc8 $11) 13... Be7 14. f4 g6 15. Bf3 Bxf3 16. Nxf3 b5 17. g4 Nf6 18. g5 Nh5 19. Bd4 O-O 20. Be5 Rad8 $11 * 

