1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. e5 Nd5 4. b3 Nc6 5. Bb2 g6 6. Bc4 {The most popular move, continuing the development.} Nf4 {This time, the main purpose of this active knight jump is to attack g2. This is not always relevant, but White needs to count with the threat ...Nxg2+.} (6... Nb6 $6 {takes the knight far from e6.} 7. Bb5 Bg7 8. O-O O-O 9. Re1 d5 10. Bxc6 bxc6 11. h3 $14 {Lombardy,W (2500) -Murey,J (2500) New York op 1985 (9) 1-0}) (6... Nc7 {offers White more freedom.} 7. Ng5 e6 8. Ne4 Bg7 9. Nd6+ Ke7 10. d4 Nxd4 {Hebbinghaus,H (2291) -Borgmeyer,M (2068) Hamburg St Pauli op-A 2010 (8) 1/2-1/2} 11. b4 b6 12. bxc5 bxc5 13. Ba3 Bxe5 14. Nxc8+ Ke8 $3 (14... Rxc8 15. Bxc5+ d6 16. Bxd4 $18) 15. c3 $14 {with dangerous initiative.}) 7. Ng5 {The same knight incursion as after ...Nc7.} (7. g3 {helps Black to regroup, while also weakening the long diagonal.} Ne6 8. h4 (8. Bxe6 dxe6 9. Qe2 b6 10. Nc3 Bb7 {Threatening ...Nd4.} 11. Rg1 Rc8 $15 12. O-O-O $6 Nd4 13. Nxd4 cxd4 14. Nb5 d3 $36) (8. Qe2 b6 9. Na3 Bb7 10. Rg1 Bg7 11. O-O-O Ned4 12. Bxd4 Nxd4 13. Nxd4 cxd4 14. Nb5 O-O 15. Nxd4 d6 $17) 8... Bg7 9. Bxe6 (9. h5 d6 $17) 9... dxe6 10. h5 Nxe5 $1 {Another way of using the weakness of the long diagonals.} 11. Bxe5 (11. Nxe5 Bxe5 12. Bxe5 Qd5 $19) 11... Bxe5 12. Nxe5 Qd4 13. f4 Qxa1 {Black has won the exchange, but his queen will be temporarily cut off play and White will retain reasonable compensation.} 14. hxg6 fxg6 15. c3 Qxa2 16. Nxg6 Rg8 17. Ne5 Bd7 ( 17... Rg7 $5) 18. Qh5+ Kd8 19. Qxh7 Kc7 20. Qxe7 Rad8 21. Kf2 Qxb3 22. Qxc5+ Kb8 23. Nf7 Rc8 24. Qd6+ Rc7 25. Ne5 Bc6 26. Nxc6+ bxc6 27. Na3 Qd5 28. Qxd5 exd5 $11 {Most of White's moves during this long sequence were "only moves".}) (7. O-O Bg7 8. Re1 {Kristof,P (2173) -Czina,P (1840) HUN-chT2 Barcza 1415 2014 1-0} d6 $17) 7... e6 (7... Nxg2+ {is premature still.} 8. Kf1 e6 9. Qg4 $13) 8. Qg4 ({White cannot continue in the same way as after ...Nc7:} 8. Ne4 $6 Nxg2+ $1 9. Kf1 Nh4 10. Nf6+ Ke7 11. Qg4 Nf5 $17 {[%cal Gc6e5,Gf8g7] Planning ...Bg7 followed by ...Nxe5!}) 8... Nh5 9. Ne4 Nd4 10. O-O d5 11. Bxd4 cxd4 12. Bb5+ Bd7 13. Bxd7+ Qxd7 14. Ng3 Nxg3 15. hxg3 {Adarsh,T (2286) -Szabo,A (2234) Budapest One Week IM 2023 (8) 1/2-1/2} Bc5 $15 * 

