{[%evp 0,42,19,19,56,56,85,85,79,37,48,31,27,27,31,19,14,-26,15,8,19,26,23,-12, 1,-2,-2,30,-8,-13,-13,-8,-22,5,32,36,43,32,32,32,43,31,31,30,37]} 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. e5 Nd5 4. c4 {An ambitious continuation, preparing a major offensive in the centre. However, it spends a tempo on driving the enemy knight closer to e6, which is the dream place for it anyway.} Nc7 5. d4 (5. Nc3 Nc6 {may transpose.} 6. d4 ({Refraining from the opening of the centre yields Black good control in that area.} 6. d3 g6 7. Bf4 Bg7 8. Qd2 Ne6 $15) 6... cxd4 7. Nxd4 {Taking the pawn is likely to yield White certain initiative, but Black can simply play as in the main line:} g6 $11) 5... cxd4 6. Nxd4 (6. Qxd4 {allows Black to gain a tempo with} Nc6 7. Qe4 (7. Qh4 d6 $11) 7... d5 { The simplest.} ({The slower} 7... g6 $5 {is also possible.} 8. Nc3 Bg7 9. Bf4 Ne6 10. Bg3 Qa5 11. Rc1 d6 12. exd6 O-O $44) 8. exd6 (8. cxd5 Qxd5 $11 { offers Black free dveelopment and good control in the centre.}) 8... Qxd6 9. Nc3 g6 {Keeping things hyper-modern.} ({An old game by the other godfather of the system went} 9... e5 {, which is entirely fine, too.} 10. Bf4 f6 11. Rd1 { Spielmann,R-Rubinstein,A Goteborg SSK 40th Anniversary Group A 1920 (9) 0-1} Qe6 12. Be3 Qf5 $11) 10. Be2 (10. Bf4 Qb4 11. O-O-O Bf5 12. Qe3 Ne6 13. Be5 f6 {Baermann,J-Robinson,W ICCF FM/2425 email 2014 0-1} 14. Bg3 Qb6 $11) 10... Bf5 11. Qh4 Bg7 12. O-O O-O 13. Bh6 {Petrova,I (2077) -Tejedor Fuente,E (2442) Titled Tuesday intern op 24th Nov blitz 2020 (4) 0-1} Rad8 14. Rad1 Qb4 15. Ng5 f6 16. Bxg7 fxg5 17. Qh6 Qxb2 18. Bxf8 Rxf8 19. Nd5 (19. Rc1 Ne6 $19 {[%cal Gc6e5,Ge5f7] followed by the other knight's transfer to f7 wins the queen.}) 19... Nxd5 20. cxd5 Ne5 {Threatening ...Nf7.} 21. Qxg5 $1 Qxe2 22. Rde1 Qb2 23. Qg3 {Black can play with two pieces for the rook in a double-edged position or else could enter a comfortable ending with} Bd3 24. Qxe5 Qxe5 25. Rxe5 Bxf1 26. Kxf1 Kf7 $11) 6... g6 7. Nc3 Bg7 8. Bf4 (8. f4 {exposes White a bit.} d6 9. exd6 Qxd6 $11 10. Ndb5 $2 (10. Be3 O-O $11) 10... Nxb5 11. Nxb5 Qxd1+ 12. Kxd1 Na6 13. Bd3 O-O 14. a3 Nc5 15. Bc2 Rd8+ 16. Ke2 Bg4+ 17. Ke3 a6 $19 {Veiga,J  (2409) -Krsnik Cohar,I (2336) Titled Tuesday intern op 20th Jun Late blitz 2023 (4) 0-1}) (8. Nf3 Nc6 9. Bf4 {transposes below.}) 8... Nc6 9. Nf3 { This is the most solid move, but not a promising one.} (9. Nxc6 $6 bxc6 10. Be2 Ne6 11. Bg3 Rb8 {faces White with serious problems.} 12. Rb1 (12. Qd2 Qa5 13. f4 d6 14. Bf3 (14. exd6 $2 Rxb2 $1 $19) 14... O-O 15. O-O dxe5 16. fxe5 Bxe5 17. Bxe5 Qxe5 $17 {Doluhanova,E (2287) -Bakunts,R (2222) Chervonograd 8th 2012 (6) 0-1}) 12... Qa5 (12... d6 $5 $146 13. exd6 Rxb2 14. Rxb2 Bxc3+ 15. Rd2 Qa5 {The pin is very unpleasant. WHite has a series of "only moves" to stay close to equality.} 16. h4 $1 {The only way of using the available tempo. At a later stage, Black will have to count with Rh3.} O-O 17. dxe7 $1 Re8 18. Bd6 $1 Nd4 ( 18... Qxa2 {would win against other moves than h2-h4, but here it runs into} 19. Rh3 $14) 19. Bf4 $1 Rxe7 20. O-O $1 Re4 21. Rxd4 $1 (21. Bh6 Bxd2 22. Bxd2 Qxd2 23. Qxd2 Nxe2+ 24. Kh2 Rxh4#) 21... Bxd4 $11 {Black has the more pleasant side of an almost equal position.}) 13. O-O (13. f4 {Dushyant,S (2370) -Baskakov,E (2215) Titled Tuesday intern op 18th Oct Early blitz 2022 (6) 0-1} d6 $17) 13... Bxe5 14. b4 Qc7 $15 {Tokhirjonova,G (2336) -Baskakov,E (2215) Titled Tuesday intern op 25th Oct Late blitz 2022 (3) 0-1}) 9... Ne6 10. Bg3 O-O 11. Be2 d6 $1 {Ensuring Black's control on d4.} (11... Re8 12. O-O d6 { is also possible.}) 12. exd6 exd6 13. O-O (13. Bxd6 Re8 14. O-O Ned4 15. Nxd4 Nxd4 16. c5 Nxe2+ 17. Nxe2 Bxb2 (17... b6 18. Nc3 Bb7 $44) 18. Rb1 Bg7 $11) ( 13. Qxd6 $6 Qa5 14. Qd2 Rd8 15. Nd5 Qxd2+ 16. Nxd2 Ned4 17. Bd3 Rxd5 18. cxd5 Nb4 19. Be4 f5 20. Bb1 Bd7 $5 $36 {There is no need to take the exchange. Black has a dangerous initiative.}) 13... Ned4 14. Nxd4 Nxd4 15. Bf3 Be6 16. b3 Nxf3+ $5 (16... f5 $6 17. Bf4 g5 18. Bd2 $14 {Kruchev,B (2263) -Grishchenko,S  (2390) Voronezh op-A 2008 (6) 0-1}) (16... Nf5 $5 17. Rc1 Qa5 18. Qd2 Nxg3 19. hxg3 Rac8 20. Bxb7 Rc7 21. Bf3 d5 $11) 17. Qxf3 Qf6 18. Qxf6 Bxf6 19. Rac1 Bxc3 20. Rxc3 d5 21. c5 Bd7 $11 * 

