1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. e5 Nd5 4. Nc3 e6 5. Nxd5 exd5 6. d4 Nc6 7. dxc5 { This looks like a concession since Black is allowed to re-capture on c5 without previously wasting time with his bishop. It is White's best chance, though since it exposes the pawn on d5.} Bxc5 8. Be2 {As mentioned earlier, the pawn on d5 is only temporarily weak. Refraining from taking it now allows Black to complete his development comfortably.} (8. Bd3 {is no better.} d6 $1 9. exd6 Qxd6 10. O-O (10. Qe2+ Kf8 $5 11. O-O Bg4 $36) 10... O-O 11. Re1 h6 12. Be3 (12. h3 Bd7 13. Be3 d4 14. Bd2 Rfe8 15. a3 Qd5 16. b4 Bd6 17. c4 dxc3 18. Rxe8+ Rxe8 19. Bxc3 Be6 $11 {So,W (2792) -Mamedyarov,S (2804) Tata Steel-A 80th 2018 (1) 1/2-1/2}) 12... Bg4 13. Bxc5 Qxc5 14. h3 {Karjakin,S (2782) -Mamedyarov,S (2808) Paris GCT blitz 2018 (18) 1/2-1/2} Bh5 15. g4 Bg6 $11 16. Bxg6 $6 fxg6 17. c3 Rf4 $36) (8. c3 {does not change much.} d6 9. Qxd5 (9. exd6 Qxd6 $11) 9... Qb6 10. Qd2 a5 $5 $146 (10... dxe5 $11 {is also good, but has the abstract drawback of allowing} 11. b4 Be7 12. Bc4) 11. exd6 $6 O-O $15 12. d7 $2 Bxd7 13. Qxd7 Bxf2+ 14. Ke2 Rfe8+ 15. Kd1 Rad8 $19) (8. Qxd5 {is the only critical move and will be examined in Lines 30 to 35.}) 8... d6 9. exd6 ( 9. Qxd5 Qa5+ 10. Qd2 (10. c3 $2 Bxf2+ $1 $19) (10. Bd2 $2 Bxf2+ $1 $19) (10. Kf1 Be6 11. Qe4 O-O-O 12. Bg5 Rd7 13. exd6 Qb6 $44) 10... Qxd2+ 11. Bxd2 dxe5 $11) 9... Qxd6 10. O-O O-O 11. c3 (11. a3 a5 $5 $11 12. Bg5 h6 13. Bh4 $6 f5 $1 {Sheremetieva,M (2260) -Vasiesiu,C (2145) ROM-chT Predeal 1997 (5) 1/2-1/2 is similar to the main line.}) 11... Re8 {Black has very pleasant play.} 12. Bg5 ( 12. Qd3 Bg4 13. Nd4 Bxd4 (13... Bxe2 14. Nxe2 Rad8 15. Bg5 Ne5 16. Qg3 f6 17. Bf4 Qa6 18. Nd4 Bxd4 19. cxd4 Nc6 20. Bh6 Re7 21. Rfe1 Rf7 $15) 14. Bxg4 Bb6 15. Bf3 Rad8 16. Bg5 $6 f6 17. Bh4 Ne5 18. Qd1 {Gavrilescu,D (2470) -Erigaisi, A (2567) Paracin Summer op 14th 2021 (5) 0-1} Nxf3+ 19. Qxf3 d4 $15 20. Qxb7 d3 $19) 12... h6 13. Bh4 f5 $1 14. Qd2 f4 $1 {The bishop is in trouble.} 15. Rfe1 Bg4 $1 {The bishop is not escaping anywhere!} (15... g5 $6 16. Nxg5 hxg5 17. Bxg5 $13 {Kovacs,Z (2269) -Sikula,V (2418) Nyiregyhaza op 2001 (9) 1-0 yielded White reasonable compensation for the piece.}) (15... Bf5 $5 16. Rad1 Be4 $19) 16. Qd3 Kh8 $1 {Preparing the next move.} 17. Rad1 Ne5 $19 18. Qxd5 Qxd5 19. Rxd5 Bxf3 20. gxf3 Nxf3+ 21. Bxf3 Rxe1+ 22. Kg2 Bb6 $19 {As if all these were not enough, Black will finally play ...g7-g5.} * 

