cannot dveelop.} 15. b4 (15. Bd3 Rxd3 16. Qxd3 Bxf2+ 17. Kf1 Rd8 18. Qe2 Rd1+ 19. Qxd1 Bc4+) 15... Bxf2+ 16. Qxf2 Rd1+ 17. Ke2 Bc4+ $19 {Giulian Jackson,R  (1989) -Ferry,E (2002) SCO-ch Hamilton 2010 (9) 0-1}) 13... O-O $1 (13... Bc5 $6 14. Ng5 $1 $14 {Ding,L (2805) -Le,T (2501) PRO League Stage rapid 2020 (7) 1/2-1/2}) 14. Be2 Rad8 15. O-O Rfe8 16. Qa4 {Jiang,Q (2246) -Meng,Y (1896) China zt 3.5 2023 (9) 1/2-1/2} Bd5 {This is the kind of adventure I mentioned earlier. Black is a pawn down and has no immediate threats. However, his marvellous development ensures him entirely adequate compensation. It is worth mentioning that Black's superior activity has some sort of "permanent" character. Whatever White tries, his pieces will not stand as well as Black's.} 17. Qc2 {Defending b2 to prepare the bishop's development.} h6 $5 {An important "quiet move", restricting the white minor pieces.} 18. Bf4 (18. Be3 Bc5 19. Bxc5 Qxc5 20. Rfd1 (20. Rad1 Qe7 21. Rd2 Bxa2 $1 $11) 20... Qe7 21. Kf1 Rd6 22. b3 Be4 23. Qc1 Rg6 $44 {with obvious compenstaion.} 24. Qe3 Qf6 25. Rac1 Re7 26. Re1 Rg4 27. h3 Rf4 {with very strong pressure.}) 18... g5 $1 19. Be3 (19. Bg3 Bf6 20. h3 Kg7 $44 {maintains Black's domination.}) 19... Bc5 20. Bxc5 Qxc5 21. Rad1 g4 22. Ne1 Qe7 23. Bd3 Qg5 $44 * 

