1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. e5 Nd5 4. Nc3 e6 5. Nxd5 exd5 6. d4 Nc6 7. dxc5 Bxc5 8. Qxd5 d6 9. exd6 Qb6 10. Qe4+ Be6 11. Qh4 Bxd6 12. Be2 O-O 13. O-O {The most natural move.} Bf5 {The only way of maintaining the initiative. It is important to prevent Bd3, of course.} 14. c3 (14. Qc4 {exposes the queen to} Rfc8 15. c3 Nb4 16. Be3 (16. Qh4 Nc2 17. Nd4 $1 Nxd4 18. Qxd4 Bc5 19. Qd5 Be6 20. Qh5 g6 21. Qf3 Re8 22. b4 Bd6 23. Bh6 Be5 24. g3 Rac8 25. Rfc1 Red8 $44) ( 16. Qb5 Qxb5 17. Bxb5 Nc2 18. Nd4 {Tarasenko,I (2144) -Babakekhyan,A (2263) Cheliabinsk Lozovatsky Memorial-A 2023 (8) 1/2-1/2} Nxd4 19. cxd4 Rc2 20. h3 h5 21. Rd1 Rac8 22. Ba4 R2c7 23. Be3 Bc2 24. Bxc2 Rxc2 $11) 16... Rxc4 17. Bxb6 Bd3 18. Bxd3 (18. Rfe1 Bxe2 19. Rxe2 axb6 20. cxb4 Bxb4 $11) 18... Nxd3 19. Rfd1 Nxb2 20. Rxd6 axb6 21. Rxb6 Na4 22. Rxb7 Nxc3 $11 23. a3 Rca4 24. h4 h6 25. Rb3 Ne4 26. g3 Nd6 27. Nd2 Nf5 28. Ra2 Nd4 29. Re3 Rc8 (29... Nb5 30. Nb1 g5 $11) 30. Kg2 Rc2 31. Re8+ Kh7 32. Rxc2 Nxc2 33. Re7 Kg8 34. Nf3 Nxa3 35. Ne5 Re4 36. Nc6 {Sousa,A (2441) -Safarli,E (2610) Monsaraz op 2023 (8) 1/2-1/2}) ( 14. Bd3 Bxd3 15. cxd3 {After creating a weak pawn in White's camp, Black can safely exchange the minor pieces, reaching a drawn ending.} Bc5 $5 (15... Be7 16. Qa4 Bc5 17. Bd2 Nd4 18. Nxd4 Bxd4 19. Bc3 Rfd8 20. Rae1 g6 21. Bxd4 Rxd4 22. Re8+ Rxe8 23. Qxe8+ Kg7 24. Qe5+ Qf6 25. Qxf6+ Kxf6 26. Rd1 Ra4 {The most convincing continuation.} (26... Rb4 27. Rd2 a5 28. Kf1 a4 29. Re2 Rd4 30. Re4 Rxe4 31. dxe4 Ke5 32. f3 Kd4 33. Ke2 g5 34. g3 b5 35. Kd2 b4 36. Ke2 g4 37. fxg4 Kxe4 38. g5 Kd4 39. Kd2 Ke4 40. Ke2 Kd4 41. Kd2 {David,A (2548) -Luther,T (2575) FRA-chT Poule Basse 2003 (8.1) 1/2-1/2}) 27. a3 Ra6 28. Kf1 Rb6 29. b4 ( 29. Rd2 Ke5 30. Ke2 h5 31. Rc2 Rb3 32. Ke3 Kd5 33. Rc7 Ke6 34. Rc2 Kd5 $11) 29... Rc6 $11) 16. b3 (16. Bd2 Nd4 17. Nxd4 Bxd4 18. Bc3 Rad8 19. Qe4 Rd6 20. Rac1 g6 $11) 16... Nd4 17. Nxd4 Bxd4 18. Rb1 {Markovic,Z (2313) -Efremov,V  (2125) Veliko Gradiste Silver Lake op-A 2022 (5) 1/2-1/2} Rac8 19. Bb2 Rfd8 $11 ) 14... Rae8 {Keeping f7 well defended.} (14... Rfe8 {is also playable.} 15. Bc4 (15. Qc4 Bg6 16. Qb5 Qc7 17. Be3 a6 18. Qb3 {Xu,Y (2507) -Le,T (2514) Titled Tuesday intern op 07th Jun Early blitz 2022 (8) 0-1} Na5 $44) 15... Qc7 $1 (15... Re4 $2 16. Bxf7+ $1) 16. Bb3 Re4 $44) 15. Qc4 {In all these lines, the white queen cannot find peace easily.} (15. Bc4 Re4 16. Qg5 Ne7 17. Bd3 Rg4 18. Qd2 Qc6 $44) 15... Bg6 16. a4 (16. Qb5 Qc7 17. Be3 a6 18. Qd5 Re6 19. Rad1 Rd8 20. Qb3 b5 21. a4 Na5 22. Qa2 Nc4 $44) 16... Na5 17. Qb5 Qc7 18. Be3 a6 19. Qd5 Be4 20. Qh5 Bc2 $5 {Reinforcing the threat ...Nb3.} (20... Nb3 21. Rad1 $14 {Dusk,J (2048) -Pareschi,R (1950) FICGS rapid A 000198 email 2017 (1) 1/2-1/2}) 21. Rac1 (21. Nd4 Bg6 22. Qh3 Nc4 23. Bc1 Na5 $5 24. Bf3 Be5 $11) (21. h3 Nb3 22. Rae1 Nc5 23. Bxc5 Bxc5 $44) 21... Bg6 22. Qh3 (22. Qd5 Be4 23. Qd1 Rd8 24. Bd4 Bd5 25. b4 Nb3 26. Rb1 Rfe8 $44) 22... Nc4 23. Bxc4 Qxc4 24. Rcd1 Bc7 25. Rd4 Qc6 26. Qd7 Be4 27. Qxc6 Bxc6 28. Rc4 Re4 29. Rxe4 Bxe4 30. Nd4 Re8 31. Re1 f6 32. f3 Bd5 33. Kf2 h5 $44 {Black's bishops' pair and the weakness of the white queenside make the position roughly equal.} * 

